.nh
.TH "OPENPASS" "1" "Apr 2026" "OpenPass" "OpenPass Manual"

.SH NAME
openpass-mcp-config - Output MCP config snippet for an AI tool


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBopenpass mcp-config  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate the MCP server configuration snippet for a specific AI tool.

.PP
The output is JSON that can be pasted into the tool's MCP configuration.
By default, outputs a stdio-based config. Use --http for HTTP-based config.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for mcp-config

.PP
\fB--http\fP[=false]
	Output HTTP-based config instead of stdio


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--vault\fP="~/.openpass"
	path to the password vault


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBopenpass(1)\fP
